        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 3:48PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Trickham, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Winchell, Trickham, Mercury, and Brookesmith.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in San Angelo.</instruction>
